/Users/andrew/dev/crimes-release-a/evals/results/0.7.2-judge/claude/refactor-06-stress-duplication.json:7:  "response": "## Confirmed duplication\n\n`crimes scan` flags `crime_00002` (near_duplicate_block, confidence 0.85): three sanitisers across `src/sanitize-a.ts`, `src/sanitize-b.ts`, and `src/sanitize-c.ts` share the same 27-line body — only the function name (`sanitizeUserInput` / `sanitizeText` / `cleanMessage`) and local variable name (`working` / `cleaned` / `normalised`) differ. The logic is identical: null/undefined → `\"\"`, trim, strip control chars, collapse whitespace, cap at 1000 chars, reject leading `<`/`>`, reject `\\x` escapes, reject >5 punctuation runs, lowercase when upper-ratio > 0.9 and length > 30.\n\n## Proposed refactor\n\nConsolidate into a single helper in a new file `src/sanitize.ts` and re-export from the three existing modules so call sites keep their current import paths during the transition.\n\n### Public API\n\n```ts\n// src/sanitize.ts\nexport interface SanitizeOptions {\n  maxLength?: number;        // default 1000\n  maxPunctuationRuns?: number; // default 5\n  upperRatioThreshold?: number; // default 0.9\n  upperRatioMinLength?: number; // default 30\n}\n\nexport function sanitize(input: unknown, options?: SanitizeOptions): string;\n```\n\n`sanitize` returns `\"\"` for null/undefined/non-coercible values and for any rejection branch (leading angle bracket, `\\x` escape, punctuation flood). Default behaviour matches the current functions exactly so the migration is a behaviour-preserving rename.\n\n### Files that change\n\n| File | Change |\n|---|---|\n| `src/sanitize.ts` *(new)* | Houses the consolidated `sanitize` + `SanitizeOptions`. |\n| `src/sanitize-a.ts` | Delete the body of `sanitizeUserInput`; re-export `export const sanitizeUserInput = sanitize;` (or remove entirely once callers are updated). Keep `assertAdminA` for now — that's a separate finding. |\n| `src/sanitize-b.ts` | Same: replace `sanitizeText` body with delegation to `sanitize`. |\n| `src/sanitize-c.ts` | Same: replace `cleanMessage` body with delegation to `sanitize`. |\n| Call sites | Anything importing the three old names continues to work via the re-export; a follow-up pass renames imports to `sanitize` from `./sanitize` and deletes the shim files. |\n\n### Why this shape\n\n- Single source of truth for the rejection rules — future tweaks (e.g. raising the 1000-char cap) land once.\n- Options object instead of positional params keeps the call sites readable and matches the existing zero-arg ergonomics (`sanitize(raw)` is unchanged).\n- `input: unknown` mirrors the runtime `String(raw)` coercion already in the code — the current `string` parameter type is a lie since the functions explicitly handle `null`/`undefined`.\n\n### Out of scope for this refactor\n\n- `crime_00001` (exact duplicate `recordSanitiseEvent` in `telemetry-a.ts` / `telemetry-b.ts`) — same playbook, different module; do it in a separate commit.\n- `crime_00003` (scattered `role === \"admin\"` checks across `assertAdminA/B/C` and `policy.ts`) — needs a `policy.ts`-owned `isAdmin(role)` helper, but the three `assertAdmin*` functions have *different* semantics (`=== \"admin\"` vs `|| \"owner\"` vs `!== \"admin\"`), so they can't be collapsed blindly. Triage call-site-by-call-site.\n- `crime_00004`/`00005` (`Date.now()` in telemetry) — orthogonal, fix when introducing a `Clock` interface.",
