/Users/andrew/dev/crimes-release-a/evals/results/0.7.5/claude/plan-06-stress-duplication.json:7:  "response": "## Refactor plan: two-step consolidation\n\n**Goal:** eliminate `crime_00002` (3× sanitiser near-duplicates) and `crime_00003` (4× `role === \"admin\"` checks) without churning either change through the other.\n\n**Ordering rationale:** policy first, sanitisers second. The role check is a primitive that the sanitisers already reach for (each sanitise-* file ships its own `assertAdmin*`). Extracting the policy first means step 2 can adopt a stable import instead of re-extracting mid-merge.\n\n---\n\n### Step 1 — Extract the admin policy\n\n**Scope:** `src/policy.ts` + 3 sanitise files (only the `assertAdmin*` helpers, not the bodies).\n\n1. In `src/policy.ts`, add `export const isAdmin = (role: string) => role === \"admin\";` as the single source of truth.\n2. Rewrite the three existing predicates to delegate: `canEditBilling`, `canSeeAuditLog`, `canImpersonate` all `return isAdmin(role);`.\n3. Delete `assertAdminA` / `assertAdminB` / `assertAdminC` from the sanitise-* files; replace any internal call sites with `isAdmin` from `./policy`.\n\n**Verify:** `crimes scan --format json | jq '.findings[] | select(.id==\"crime_00003\")'` returns nothing. Sanitiser duplication (`crime_00002`) should still report — confirms step 1 didn't accidentally touch the bodies.\n\n**Commit:** \"extract isAdmin policy; collapse 4 call sites\".\n\n---\n\n### Step 2 — Consolidate the sanitisers\n\n**Scope:** new `src/sanitize.ts` + delete sanitize-a/b/c bodies.\n\n1. Create `src/sanitize.ts` exporting a single `sanitize(raw: string): string` containing the shared 30-line body (trim → strip control chars → length cap → leading-bracket reject → escape-sequence reject → punctuation-spam reject → upper-case normalisation). The bodies are byte-identical aside from renamed locals, so no behavioural merging is required.\n2. Replace `sanitize-a.ts` / `sanitize-b.ts` / `sanitize-c.ts` with thin re-exports under their original names (`sanitizeUserInput`, `sanitizeText`, `cleanMessage`) so external imports keep resolving. If a follow-up cleanup is acceptable, drop the re-export shims and update call sites directly — but that's a separate change, not part of this two-step plan.\n3. The role-check imports added in step 1 stay put; they're now imports against a stable `isAdmin`.\n\n**Verify:** `crimes scan --format json | jq '.summary'` drops `crime_00002`. Only the `recordSanitiseEvent` duplicate (`crime_00001`) and the two `Date.now()` findings remain — both explicitly out of scope for this plan.\n\n**Commit:** \"consolidate sanitisers behind shared `sanitize()`\".\n\n---\n\n**What's deliberately not in scope:** `crime_00001` (telemetry duplicate) and `crime_00004/5` (Temporal Recklessness). Folding them in would muddy the diff and the telemetry duplicate wants a clock-injection design conversation rather than a mechanical extract.",
