poral Recklessness in billing.ts, reinforced by `crime_00011` and `crime_00030` showing the existing billing tests assert nothing.\n\nSeven `Date.now()` / `new Date()` calls in invoice generation means proration windows, due-date math, and audit timestamps all read the wall clock at call time. With the test suite already weak (one zero-assert test, one with only weak matchers), there's no safety net to catch a regression introduced when you do (1) and (2). Threading a `clock: () => Date` parameter (or a module-level injected `now()`) through `generateInvoice` is cheap, unblocks meaningful tests on the extracted helpers, and lets you delete the cross-cutting `crime_00009` finding in one pass rather than chasing each `Date.now()` individually after the split.\n\n**Order matters:** do (3) before (1) so the extracted helpers can be tested deterministically as you pull them out, and do (2) standalone — it doesn't depend on the split and the misleading-name risk is too sharp to leave sitting while you refactor around it.",
