/Users/andrew/dev/crimes-release-a/evals/results/0.9.3/claude/review-01-messy-ts-app.json:7:  "response": "# Review: `01-messy-ts-app` PR\n\n37 findings (4 high / 15 medium / 18 low). My verdict is **block merge** — 6 findings would, on their own, justify a return. Categorisation below uses severity + `agent_risk`; ties broken by whether the issue is objectively broken in any environment vs. eventually-painful.\n\n## Block merge (6)\n\n| ID | Charge | Sev | agent_risk | Why block |\n|---|---|---|---|---|\n| 00001 | SVG With Embedded Raster | high | 0.70 | High sev + the asset is actively lying about being vector. Ship as PNG or re-author. |\n| 00002 | God Function `generateInvoice` (204 lines) | high | 0.55 | Sev 0.90, billing code. \"Edit one section, miss the interactions\" is exactly the agent-risk this tool flags. |\n| 00003 | Temporal Recklessness in `date.ts` (8 calls) | high | 0.62 | Sev 0.80 + the highest agent_risk in the report. Non-deterministic domain code; tests can't pin a moment without monkey-patching. |\n| 00004 | Half-UTC, Half-Local on same receiver | high | 0.61 | Sev 0.80, agent_risk 0.61. Silent bug — offsets by the host's UTC offset, the kind of thing that passes CI in one tz and breaks in prod. |\n| 00006 | Hardcoded `localhost:3000` in `src/api/files.ts` | medium | 0.53 | Severity reads \"medium\" but the literal is objectively broken in any non-dev environment. Block on correctness, not on score. |\n| 00007 | Hardcoded `/Users/andrew/dev/crimes/schema.json` | medium | 0.53 | Same logic as 00006 — works on exactly one machine. Trivial fix (`os.homedir()`), zero reason to merge as-is. |\n\n## Warn (18)\n\nReal issues, surface in PR comments, fix in follow-ups. Grouped to keep the table short.\n\n**Correctness-adjacent (agent_risk 0.46–0.58)** — should be on a backlog before they bite:\n- 00009 Temporal Recklessness in `billing.ts` (medium, 0.46) — same class as 00003 but in invoice code; downgraded because tests already exist for the file\n- 00010 Timezone Roulette — 2 unzoned `new Date(\"…\")` parses in `date.ts` (medium, 0.53)\n- 00014 DST-Naive Day Math (`+ 86_400_000`) (medium, 0.52)\n- 00013 `calculateRefundPreview` does I/O — name lies (medium, 0.44). Pure-sounding name on a side-effecting function is a classic agent trap.\n\n**Multi-source-of-truth / drift (agent_risk 0.49–0.58)** — high agent_risk because these are exactly what an agent updates partially:\n- 00015 Concept Alias Drift: tenant/account/organisation/team/workspace across 5 files (medium, 0.58)\n- 00012 `\"enterprise\"` literal scattered across 4 production files (medium, 0.52)\n- 00018 Duplicated nav source — `/settings/billing` labelled \"Plans\" vs \"Billing\" (medium, 0.49)\n- 00020 Route Metadata Drift — 4 competing labels for `/settings/billing` (medium, 0.49)\n\n**Hidden / weak intent (agent_risk 0.42–0.49)**:\n- 00005 Missing Agent Context — no AGENTS.md/CLAUDE.md/SKILL.md (medium, 0.53). Worth fixing first since it raises the agent_risk floor for everything else.\n- 00011 Test \"renders the enterprise plan\" has zero asserts (medium, 0.46)\n- 00017 Comment encodes a refund rule the code doesn't (medium, 0.42)\n- 00019 TODO density 424/kLOC in `src/todo.ts` (medium, 0.49) — 42× threshold; either ship a real implementation or delete the stub\n- 00016 `billing.ts` 310 lines vs 300 threshold (medium, 0.42). Just over the line, but pairs with 00002.\n\n**Lower-impact, still worth flagging**:\n- 00022 Docs-Code Drift — broken `./setup.md` link (low, 0.51)\n- 00023 Sync I/O (`existsSync`, `statSync`, `readFileSync`) in `loadPlanSchema` (low, 0.44)\n- 00024 One `Date.now()` in `src/api/state.ts` (low, 0.44)\n- 00036/37/38 Three orphaned routes (`/account/subscription`, `/team`, `/workspace/members`) (low, 0.39). Either link them or delete them — orphaned destinations correlate with the alias-drift finding in 00015.\n\n## Ignore (13)\n\nStyle / preference / low signal. Don't gate the PR; let the author choose.\n\n- 00021 254 KB hero PNG, 00025 32×32 PNG icon — perf chores\n- 00026 `+`-concat date format, 00027 `toLocaleDateString()` no locale — same `date.ts` rewrite as 00003 will sweep these\n- 00028, 00029 Unprefixed booleans (`paid`, `expired`, `stale`, `disableBilling`, `skipRetry`)\n- 00030 Weak-matcher assertion in `creates an invoice` test\n- 00031 `options` bag in `describeCheckout`\n- 00032 Return-shape roulette in `resolvePaymentResult` (borderline — could move to Warn if `petty.ts` is on a public boundary)\n- 00033 `!disableBilling && !skipRetry` double-negative\n- 00034 `users: User` / `invoice: Invoice[]` plural mismatch\n- 00035 Four TODOs in `billing.ts` (12.9/kLOC, just over threshold)\n\n## Rationale for the cutoffs\n\n- **Block** = severity high, *or* the issue is broken-in-every-other-environment (00006, 00007), *or* agent_risk ≥ 0.60 (00001, 00003, 00004). All four of those gates fire on real bugs, not style.\n- **Warn** = medium severity, or low severity with agent_risk ≥ 0.42 *and* multi-file drift. These represent debt the agent_risk score is specifically designed to surface — they don't fail tests today but they raise the cost of every subsequent edit.\n- **Ignore** = severity ≤ 0.30 and agent_risk ≤ 0.45 and self-contained (single file, single line, no drift). Cosmetic; pick them up opportunistically.\n\nBottom line: the four high-severity findings plus the two hardcoded paths are blocking. The drift cluster (00012, 00015, 00018, 00020, 00036–38) is the most interesting *agent-specific* signal here — they're all medium/low severity but they're the exact shape of damage an autonomous editor does when it touches \"billing\" or \"team\" without seeing every alias.",
