ember\" | string;\n\nexport function isAdmin(role: Role): boolean;          // role === \"admin\"\nexport function canEditBilling(role: Role): boolean;   // delegates to isAdmin\nexport function canSeeAuditLog(role: Role): boolean;   // delegates to isAdmin\nexport function canImpersonate(role: Role): boolean;   // delegates to isAdmin\n```\nReconcile the three drifting `assertAdmin*` shapes deliberately: `assertAdminB`'s \"admin OR owner\" and `assertAdminC`'s negation each need a product call — pick the intended semantics per call site rather than preserving the accidental divergence. Delete `assertAdminA/B/C`.\n\n### 3. `src/telemetry.ts` — single event recorder with injected clock\n```ts\nexport interface Clock { now(): number; }\nexport const systemClock: Clock = { now: () => Date.now() };\n\nexport interface SanitiseEvent {\n  originalLength: number;\n  sanitisedLength: number;\n  reductionRatio: number;\n  timestamp: number;\n}\n\nexport function recordSanitiseEvent(\n  originalLength: number,\n  sanitisedLength: number,\n  clock: Clock = systemClock,\n): void;\n```\nClock injection resolves `crime_00004`/`00005` in one place.\n\n## Files that change\n\n| File | Change |\n|---|---|\n| `src/sanitize.ts` | **new** — consolidated `sanitize()` |\n| `src/sanitize-a.ts` | delete (callers updated to `sanitize`) |\n| `src/sanitize-b.ts` | delete |\n| `src/sanitize-c.ts` | delete |\n| `src/telemetry.ts` | **new** — consolidated `recordSanitiseEvent` with injectable `Clock` |\n| `src/telemetry-a.ts` | delete |\n| `src/telemetry-b.ts` | delete |\n| `src/policy.ts` | rewrite around `isAdmin`; existing `canEditBilling` / `canSeeAuditLog` / `canImpersonate` delegate |\n| any call sites of the old symbols | update imports (out of scope for the fixture; in a real repo, grep first) |\n\nNet effect: **−6 files, +2 files, 1 rewrite**, and all three duplication findings plus both `direct_date` findings collapse to zero.",
