ces`.\n6. **`index.ts`** barrel last, after every move has type-checked individually.\n\nRun `crimes scan src/billing --format json` between step 2 and step 5 to confirm `agent_risk` on `generateInvoice` is unchanged (this is a *file* split, not a *function* split — the God Function and its 7 `Date.now()`/`new Date()` sites at lines 57/63/92/198/238/250/273 will still be there).\n\n## Callers that update\n\n- **In-repo: none.** `grep` for `from \"…/billing\"` and for the five exported symbol names returns zero hits outside `billing.ts` itself. The placeholder `src/billing.test.ts` does not import the real module (the test is `crime_00011` / `crime_00030` — proves nothing).\n- **Intra-file:** `generateInvoice` lines **145–154** (tax block) → call `tax(user.country, afterDiscount)`. Lines **91–102** (loyalty block) → call the new `daysSince(user)` helper. These are the only edits where the file-split actually changes behavior wiring.\n- **External (if any future caller exists):** preserved through `src/billing/index.ts` barrel; `import { generateInvoice } from \"./billing\"` keeps working because Node/TS resolves `./billing` → `./billing/index.ts`.\n\n## What this plan deliberately does **not** do\n\nPer the crimes skill's auto-fix policy, I am surfacing — not executing. Three things stay out of scope of *this* split:\n\n- Breaking up `generateInvoice` itself (`crime_00002`, `agent_risk 0.66`) — that's a function-level refactor and needs its own change with real tests; `src/billing.test.ts` currently asserts nothing on it.\n- Injecting a clock to retire the 7 `Date.now()`/`new Date()` calls (`crime_00009`).\n- Renaming `calculateRefundPreview` to disclose its side effects (`crime_00013`) or encoding the L39 prose rule (`crime_00017`).\n\nEach of those is a separate, riskier change that this file-split makes *possible* (smaller surface per edit) without doing.",
